# No New Java

This codebase is being migrated from Java to Kotlin. Do not:
- Create new `.java` files in `src/main/java/` or `src/test/java/`
- Use Java-style getter/setter patterns when Kotlin properties work
- Use `Optional<T>` when nullable types (`T?`) are available
- Use Java streams when Kotlin collection functions (`map`, `filter`, `firstOrNull`) are available
- Use field injection (`@Autowired` on fields) -- use constructor injection
- Use `public` modifier (it's the default in Kotlin)
- Use data classes for JPA entities (only for DTOs that are not JPA-managed)
- Write explicit no-arg constructors for `@Entity` classes (the `kotlin-jpa` plugin handles this)
- Manually add `open` to Spring-annotated classes (the `kotlin-spring` plugin handles this)

Write idiomatic Kotlin. When in doubt, read `.cursor/skills/kotlin-migration/SKILL.md`.

**Exception**: Generated code in `target/generated-sources/` is Java and stays Java. Do not convert it.
